THE OSI MODEL


1.  P lease     PHYSICAL - data cables, cat6
2.  D o         DATA - switching, MAC
3.  N ot        NETWORK - IP, routing
4.  T hrow      TRANSPORT - TCP/UDP
5.  S ausage    SESSION - session management
6.  P izza      PRESENTATION - WMV, JPEG, MOV
7.  A way       APPLICATION - HTTP, SMTP


Note : We receive data from the physical layer all the way down to the application layer and vice versa for sending data
     : For troubleshooting go from physical to appplication layer
      